HEADWORD: Interjacency
<hw>In`ter*ja"cen*cy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Interjacent</er>.]</ety> <def>The state of being between; a coming
or lying between or among; intervention; also, that which lies
between.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>England and Scotland is divided only by the
<qex>interjacency</qex> of the Tweed.</q> <rj><qau>Sir M.
Hale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interjacent</ent>⟦br⟧
